<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n16039k"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n16" href="#n16039k">N16 (VI.D.1)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n16all.htm#n16039k"> 39(k)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Chaperon</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">So, under steadily flattening vaults, shallower mouldings&mdash;this is the period of the caveto&mdash;sparser, more mechanical ornament&mdash;witness the square and the &lsquo;Tudor&rsquo; foliage&mdash;through windows of stiffened mullions and, by order of the specialised glazier, ever more inorganic design, man may be seen inventing this fantastic hat, the &lsquo;<mark>Chaperon</mark>,&rsquo; whose fashionable points were remnants of its past uses, and to match it a gown, the houpelande, to accentuate his figure. <small> D. Heard, <a name="HEARD" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#HEARD"><cite title="source">Narcissus, an Anatomy of Clothes</cite></a> (1924) 90</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c02161k" href="c02all.htm#c02161k">VI.C.02:161(k)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
